2.Description: We need a crossbar interconnect that supports the default peripherals and the simple bus implementation we're using

3.Description: We need to support Axi4 Lite to allow use with other Axi4 Lite IP

4.Title: Implement Fence Instruction
4.Description: Fence instructions are not yet implemented and are necessary

5.Title: Test Existing IP on Hardware
5.Description: The current implementation could work on hardware, test it

6.Title: Implement CSRs
6.Description: We need CSRs to be able to implement more complicated programs

7.Title: Create SDK
7.Description: We need an SDK to make development easier

8.Title: Create Testbenches for Existing IP
8.Description: We need testbenches to verify that all IP works as expected

9.Title: Implement Cache System
9.Description: We need to be able to cache data in local onboard memory

10.Title: Add Filtering to Cache System
10.Description: Current cache does not filter requests for addresses that should not be cached, add support for cache filtering

11.Title: Implement Branch Prediction Unit
11.Description: Had an idea for a branch prediction unit that was based on a cachelike implementation - when a branch occurs, the old PC and new PC are logged so that the next time the old PC occurs, the unit will guess the new PC. If incorrect, the same as now occurs, but if correct, we don't have to drop the first few clock cycles. Would also be fun to measure the improvement as well.

12.Title: Rearchitect Branches/Jumps to Execute Stage
12.Description: Currently we have branches/jumps at the memaccess stage, move it to the execute stage to reduce cost incurred  by missed branches/jumps

13.Title: Reduce Size of Pipeline
13.Description: The pipeline is 6+ stages. This is ridiculous. Reduce it to 5 stages to reduce cost.

14.Title: Add M Extension Instructions
14.Description: In order for this CPU to be useful, it needs to have a multiplier and divider unit. This gets us closer to rv32imaf, which would be pretty powerful for a multipurpose microcontroller core
